title: For Sale:  Tracking Point XS1 .338 Lapua Magnum Surgeon Rifle
postcontent:
Tracking Point XS1 - come by the store and take a look. This is the real deal.



This Precision-Guided Firearm enables high-impact shots beyond what elite marksmen can achieve.  Your extreme-distance shots will be beyond belief—even with fast-moving targets.

Perfect impact on targets out to 0.75 miles, moving as fast as 20 miles per hour
The same Tag-and-Shoot™ technology found in fighter jets
Advanced target tracking technology
Comprehensive, purpose-built shooting system

Tag-and-Shoot™

Tag-and-Shoot is how a shooter actually uses a Precision-Guided Firearm. The shooter puts the reticle on the intended point of impact, presses the tag button, and then pulls the trigger when he has moved on to the designated point of impact. The Precision-Guided Firearm does the rest.

TriggerLink™

TriggerLink is an electronic connection between the tracking optic and the guided trigger. The tracking optic communicates with the guided trigger to ensure that the round is released at the precise moment required to make an extraordinary shot.

Permanent Zero

The shooter never again has to worry about whether his gun is properly zeroed. The Precision-Guided Firearm’s laser-based barrel reference system maintains a permanent, factory-set, perfect zero for every shot. It’s unaffected by shock, vibration, or other environmental factors.

Virtual Rest

Virtual Rest™ makes off-hand shots as easy as shooting from a stable rest. The Precision-Guided Firearm image is stabilized, so you can Tag-and-Shoot™ moving or stationary targets at extreme distances from an off-hand position.

Heads Up Display

HUD is the digital display that shows the field of view. The key user-interface between the shooter and the Precision-Guided Firearm, the HUD displays vital pieces of data including range-to-target, target velocity, shot angle, compass heading, gun cant, battery status, WiFi status, wind velocity and direction, kill zone size, ammunition type, temperature, barometric pressure, and time of day.

title: For Sale:  Mini Mosin Nagant - One of a Kind, Unique and SHORT
postcontent:
Bubba got to this, but it'll still hold at least minute-of-dinner-plate.  It's a very handy gun with an impressive fireball, launching the cheap and powerful 7.62x54r.  That's right, the Mosin Nagant: because sometimes people hide behind things.

The barrel has been cut down to 16.25" giving it an overall length of less than 36" - barely longer than an M4.  The picture shows an M4 and a full size Mosin Nagant for comparison (though neither of them are for sale).  It was also given an 11* target crown and has a limb saver recoil pad installed - it is a blast to shoot.  I wouldn't hesitate to use it for hogs, aircraft carriers or just scaring people in the next county.  Unfortunately, I have to move into a smaller place soon and so I have to cut down on the number of toys I have.

Mosins are going for around 180-200 these days, which seems criminal to me.  I won't take a dime over $125 for this piece.

I am willing to look at trades, but I am mostly looking for an inexpensive snub nose or short barreled revolver in .38, .357 or 9mm.  We can balance a trade with cash if need be.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Fusion Firearms Custom 1911 .45 ACP New Unfired
postcontent: I am considering letting go of one of my safe queens which is a custom, built to my specs, Fusion Firearms 5" 1911 built by Bob Serva of Fusion Firearms.  I ordered it approximately 3 years ago and the build process takes about 1.5 years so the pistol has been in my possession for approximately 1.5 years.  As stated it is brand new and only test fired upon completion of the build.  The build specs are too many to list but I will do my best.  After owning several other brands of 1911's and being disappointed with the overall quality, I decided to move up to a custom pistol and after much research into other brands such as Wilson Combat, Les Baer, Ed Brown, etc., I settled on Fusion.  I am happy I did and wouldn't change a thing.  I am only considering parting with it because I would rather not have so much money tied up in one firearm that I do not actually use.  Once you rack the slide on this firearm and feel how the slide seems to be on ball bearings you will immediately recognize the quality that you only get from a custom 1911.  No Kimber compares.  As far as "off the shelf" 1911's go, the only one that would even come remotely close would be the Dan Wesson Valor which coincidently was designed by Bob Serva when he owned Dan Wesson before selling it to CZ and starting his own company.  My specs for this 1911 were intended for it to be a fighting or duty 1911 so it is entirely black (Satin/Matte Black Shield PVD on slide frame small parts and even the barrel) except for the hand selected cocobolo slim grips.  It has a magwell, XS sights, match grade barrel, ambi safety, extended mag release, checkered front strap, sure-grip slide serrations on the rear only, custom tuned trigger that breaks at a crisp 3.75 -4.25 lbs, recessed slide stop pin, full length guide rod, and the barrel is target crowned and flush cut, and the top of the slide and back of the rear sites are grooved to provent glare.  All edges have been softened for carry. It comes with an additional XS front tritium sight, case, and three magazines all tested for function by Fusion.  As for it's value, when I ordered it the total package was $1,800 and I assume they have gone up since then. If you are in the market for a high end 1911 this one is ready without the wait and is more than worth considering.  Don't pay for a name, pay for quality.  VERY SERIOUS inquiries only by PHONE CALL ONLY.  NO TEXT OR EMAILS WILL BE REPLIED TO.  I will email or text pics after we have a phone conversation so please do not email asking for them.  I will get them posted asap but am not willing to deal with emails and text.  I may be contacted at 8 six 5- three 2 three- 44 one 9.  I will require a bill of sale to be signed and prefer to deal with valid permit carriers only.  $1,800 value but will entertain reasonable offers.  No low ballers as I do not NEED to sell.  I am willing to listen to reasonable cash offers or cash plus any of the items listed as trade interest.   Thanks for looking!
